ce:section.ce:para:
Functional monomers play a pivotal role in the selectivity and binding affinity of Zn/Co-MOF@MIPs, thus necessitating the optimization of the molar ratio between the template and functional monomers. Optimal amounts of functional monomers are instrumental in constructing effective recognition sites, thereby facilitating the attainment of optimal imprinting factors and exceptional rebinding ability [21]. Consequently, the optimal molar ratio of template to functional monomer was determined to be 1:8 (
                           Fig. S1
                        ). It's noteworthy that all subsequent discussions on Zn/Co-MOF@MIPs were conducted under these optimized preparation conditions.
